text: Milena Vicenová Milena Vicenová (born 12 August 1955, in Přerov) is a former Minister of Agriculture of the Czech Republic. After that she became an EU project manager of the Technology Agency of the Czech Republic.Agrarian Perspectives XXIV. She had also been the Czech Ambassador to the European Union.Radio == References == Category:Agriculture ministers of the Czech Republic Category:Czech diplomats Category:1955 births Category:Living people Category:Civic Democratic Party (Czech Republic) Government ministers Category:People from Přerov
